Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

2024-12-19

Cymbopogon citratus

Photo by Dinesh Valke, licensed under CC-BY-SA 2.0

Assembly is allelic, and the genome is tetraploid. It has a haploid genome size of 1200 Mb, and has 20 haploid chromosomes.

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Cymbopogon citratus from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Figure 1 from the main text, with Cymbopogon citratus highlighted with colored points.

Highlighted Figure 2

Figure 2 from the main text, with Cymbopogon citratus highlighted with colored points.

Dotplot of Cymbopogon citratus vs. Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Cymbopogon citratus along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Cymbopogon citratus is a tetraploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 4 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Cymbopogon citratus

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Cymbopogon citratus along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Cymbopogon citratus is a tetraploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 4 lines for each subgenome.
